On January 17, 2020, President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation honoring the life and accomplishments of Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. The proclamation highlights Dr. King's role in shaping the Civil Rights Movement, fighting against discrimination, and inspiring millions with his message of peaceful protest and nonviolent resistance. It also emphasizes America's promise of freedom and justice, rooted in the inalienable rights of mankind. President Trump reaffirms his commitment to protecting and expanding freedom and opportunity for all Americans, regardless of race or any other barriers. The proclamation concludes by urging all Americans to engage in acts of service to others, their community, and the nation, in honor of Dr. King's dream.